
## RTL Agent Output Defaults

When the user writes in Hebrew, Arabic, Persian, or Yiddish, or asks for output in one of those languages, format final answers using these rules:

- Wrap RTL prose in `<div dir="rtl" align="right">` containers when Markdown/HTML is supported.
- Keep code blocks, shell commands, logs, JSON, YAML, diffs, file paths, branch names, and identifiers outside RTL containers and LTR.
- Put inline LTR tokens in backticks.
- Avoid Markdown tables for mixed RTL/LTR content unless truly useful.
- Do not use invisible Unicode bidi controls by default.
- Do not claim this changes the IDE/chat UI; it only formats the agent's own output.
